    CurrentBody = @"<p><b>Parallel testing</b> executes multiple tests simultaneously, dramatically reducing total suite execution time. Instead of running 100 tests sequentially in 50 minutes, you can run them in 10 minutes across 5 parallel threads.</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><b>NUnit [Parallelizable]:</b> Attribute to run tests concurrently at assembly, fixture, or test level.</li>
                        <li><b>ParallelScope.All:</b> Runs both fixtures and tests within them in parallel — maximum concurrency.</li>
                        <li><b>ParallelScope.Fixtures:</b> Runs test fixtures in parallel, but tests within each fixture run sequentially.</li>
                        <li><b>Thread Safety:</b> Each parallel test must have its <b>own WebDriver instance</b>. Sharing a driver causes race conditions and flaky failures.</li>
                        <li><b>[LevelOfParallelism(N)]:</b> Assembly-level attribute that caps concurrent threads (e.g., 4 threads).</li>
                        <li><b>ThreadLocal&lt;IWebDriver&gt;:</b> Ensures each thread gets its own isolated driver instance.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Parallel execution is essential for CI/CD pipelines where fast feedback loops are critical.</p>";

